The Bits in Bio Education Compendium is run entirely by a team of volunteers. Our members include students, researchers, and industry professionals. Read on below to get to know us. If you'd like to connect or join us, check out the [Contribute](contribute.qmd) page!

<style>
.team-grid {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); /* exactly 3 columns */
  gap: 2rem;
  text-align: center;
  justify-items: center;
}
@media (max-width: 700px) {
  .team-grid {
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); /* 2 per row on tablets */
  }
}
@media (max-width: 500px) {
  .team-grid {
    grid-template-columns: 1fr; /* stack vertically on small screens */
  }
}
.team-member img {
  width: 120px;
  height: 120px;
  border-radius: 50%;
  object-fit: cover;
  margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
}
.team-member strong {
  display: block;
  margin-top: 0.25rem;
  font-size: 1.1em;
}
.team-member p {
  margin: 0.25rem 0 0;
  font-size: 0.95em;
}
</style>

